{
  "intro": "Tener que plus an infinitive is the most common way to say that someone has to do something in Spanish. The second verb stays in the infinitive form.",
  "overview": {
    "body": "Conjugate tener for the subject, add que, and then use an infinitive such as estudiar, trabajar, comer, or salir.",
    "use_note": "basic infinitives with tener que"
  },
  "examples": [
    {
      "spanish": "Tengo que estudiar.",
      "english": "I have to study."
    },
